   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER TWO THE NEW MAN</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>CREATED BY CHRIST IN HIMSELF</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>AND ENLIVENED BY GOD WITH CHRIST AS LIFE,</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>AS THE POEM, THE MASTERPIECE, OF GOD Scripture Reading: Eph 2:14-22, 4-10 OUTLINE Created by Christ Eph 2:14-22: In Himself as the sphere and element substantially v. 15.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>By slaying the enmity the issue of the different ordinances in living and worship through the cross v. 16b.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Putting the two Israel and the Gentiles into one Body v. 16a.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>To be God's household and God's kingdom v. 19.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Being built together into a dwelling place of God in spirit vv.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>20-22: Upon the foundation of the apostles and prophets v. 20a.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>With Christ as the joining cornerstone v. 20b.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Enlivened by God vv.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>4-10: With Christ as life organically vv.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>5-6: Making the members constituents of the new man alive together with Christ v. 5.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>Raising them up together with Christ v. 6a.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>Seating them together with Christ in the heavenlies v. 6b.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>By grace through faith v. 8: By grace by having the processed Triune God dispensed into the believers.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>Through faith through Christ moving in the believers as their faith, their substantiating ability to apprehend the divine favor given to them in Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>To be the poem, the masterpiece, of God v. 10: To show forth the wisdom in God's grace cf. v. 7; 3:10.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>And to have a new man walk in the good works which God prepared for him beforehand.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>That God might display in the ages to come the surpassing riches of His grace toward the believers in Christ 2:7.</S>
   </TEXT>
